Here is the synopsis, "A fictional film set in the alluring world of one of the most stunning scandals to rock our nation, American Hustle tells the story of brilliant con man Irving Rosenfeld (Christian Bale), who along with his equally cunning and seductive British partner Sydney Prosser (Amy Adams) is forced to work for a wild FBI agent Richie DiMaso (Bradley Cooper). DiMaso pushes them into a world of Jersey powerbrokers and mafia that's as dangerous as it is enchanting. Jeremy Renner is Carmine Polito, the passionate, volatile, New Jersey political operator caught between the con-artists and Feds. Irving's unpredictable wife Rosalyn (Jennifer Lawrence) could be the one to pull the thread that brings the entire world crashing down. Like David O. Russell's previous films, American Hustle defies genre, hinging on raw emotion, and life and death stakes. (c) Sony"

Comment:
Matthew's Movie Madness

"American Hustle" (2013)
Rating: 10/10

David O. Russell. I never heard of him until I saw this movie and "Silver Linings Playbook". Now, I can't get enough of him. This film's f**king awesome! This and "The Wolf of Wall Street" are two of the best films of 2013.

Major reason to watch this? The cast. Yes, I'm making this joke, but it's a good joke. When you got Batman, Rocket Racoon, Lois Lane, Hawkeye, and Katniss Everdeen in the same frickin' flick, you know it should be awesome. Christian Bale, Bradley Cooper, Amy Adams, Jeremy Renner, and Jennifer Lawrence make up a good ensemble, and all five of them share things only David O. Russell could bring out in them: grand performances, an equal share in comedy and drama, and an incredible character arc. Even if the story seems flustered, they keep the film afloat.

Honestly, if you haven't seen this, word of advice: watch this. You won't be disappointed.

Title: American Hustle Official TRAILER 1 (2013) - Bradley Cooper, Jennifer Lawrence Movie HD
Comment:
this was a bad ass movie !!! great plot, great characters, great acting, great twist at the ending.
the classic rock music throughout, from numerous 70's famous mega-hit bands, was also great.

several other comments posted here, said they found this movie boring, or they did not like it, etc....

i suspect most of those were likely younger viewers.

years ago, i heard the same from my younger teenage cousins & nephews, about movies like Jackie Brown & Fargo. (which i told them i felt were very good movies). ¬†now that they are all adults, some of them have re-watched those flicks, and then told me they now agree with me, & think both movies are very good.

i think the older a person is, the more likely they are going to find movies such as Jackie Brown, Fargo, & American Hustle here, to be more interesting & see the real life details of the storyline & see the superb quality of all the characters & their interactions with one another, etc.

a younger viewer likely just sees these type flicks as somewhat slow & boring, because these type movies are not constantly capturing the viewer interest with excitement, like a lot of the common faster paced modern adventure movies, disaster movies, or crime movies do.

i suspect anyone 20 to 25 yrs old or younger, that didn't like this movie now.... if they go back & watch this movie 10 yrs from now, when they will obviously have an older perspective, then they will likely find this movie much better, than you consider it to be now.

Comment: When I first saw this movie I didn't like it too much, maybe that's because I saw The Wolf of Wall Street the night before which is 10 times more entertaining (in my opinion of course). Also because the trailers fooled me into thinking I was going to have a Goodfellas-esque film with violence and some sexy girls but ended up with a film that's extremely dialogue-laden with a really confusing plot (not that I don't love dialogue, Quentin Tarantino is my favorite writer/director largely because of his incredible dialogue). But after seeing it again, I have to say it is actually quite good. Fantastic acting, very good character development, great soundtrack, sharp dialogue. I'm glad it did so well and got all of those accolades, but the reason I would't give it an excellent mark is that it didn't entertain me from start to finish, some parts were kinda boring. I'd give it something like a 7.5/10.

Title: American Hustle Official TRAILER 1 (2013) - Bradley Cooper, Jennifer Lawrence Movie HD
Comment: American Hustle is golden cinema and a movie that should be treasured. So sick of all of the complaints about how it's "boring" or to just see it for the performances. These are such obvious criticisms that really don't look beyond the surface to see the complexity and beauty of what David O. Russell has achieved here. A movie that portrays self-delusion and reinvention better than any film in recent memory, and does it with fabulous style and flair. A movie that captures the nature of how one might become a con artist, but also is tragically honest in showing the images and appearances of happiness we create for ourselves in order to escape our insecurities and sorrow. (It is no wonder these characters are con artists). It is already hard to achieve this kind of depth on a dramatic level, but American Hustle masterfully presents these themes through comedy... which is truly impressive. It is hilarious, sad, and true. The film is also amazing just on a level of craft. The music, the editing, the make-up and hairstyling, ugh. It's a blissful, wonderful experience and anyone who just comments on all of the clips and trailers it has just for the purpose of hating on it is such a bummer that please, do all of the fans a favor and keep it to yourself. Of course it's your own opinion and thats fine but I hate going back to this trailer that I love so much just to see people commenting everywhere "THIS MOVIE SUCKED. ITS SOOOOO OVERRATED AND BORING." Just please, no.
